problem link: https://leetcode.com/problems/letter-combinations-of-a-phone-number/description/
Intuition
we use backtracking to generate all possible letter combinations.
A hash map stores the mapping of each digit(2-9) to its corresponding letters on a phone keypad.

we recursively process one digit at a time.

at each recursive call:
i represents the current digit being processed, diary stores the letters chosen so far.

for the current digit we iterate through all possible letters, for each letter , add it to diary , recursively process the next digit . Remove the letter to restore previous state backtracking.

when i reaches the length of input string we have formed one complete letter combination so we will add it to the answer.

if the input string is empty , we return an empty list since there are no possible combinations

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n*4^n) In the worst case, each of the n digits has 4 choices.
There are at most 4ⁿ combinations.
Constructing each combination using "".join(curr) takes O(n) time.

Space complexity:
Auxiliary Space: O(n)
The recursion stack and the curr list can grow to at most n characters.
Output Space: O(n × 4ⁿ)
Required to store all generated combinations.

Code
class Solution:
    def letterCombinations(self, digits: str) -> List[str]:
        hash_map = {}
        hash_map[2] = "abc"
        hash_map[3] = "def"
        hash_map[4] = "ghi"
        hash_map[5] = "jkl"
        hash_map[6] = "mno"
        hash_map[7] = "pqrs"
        hash_map[8] = "tuv"
        hash_map[9] = "wxyz"
        
        diary = []
        result = []
        n = len(digits)
        def fun(i):
            if n == 0:
                return []
                
            if i == n:
                result.append("".join(diary))
                return
            
            string_choice = hash_map[int(digits[i])]
            for j in range(len(string_choice)):
                diary.append(string_choice[j])
                fun(i+1)
                diary.pop()
        fun(0)
        return result
